<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="N" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Net" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Net,</orth> a texture used to catch fish, birds, and other animals: <bibl n="shak. ven 67" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.221" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 221</bibl> <cit><quote>(spread).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.62" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 62</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.203" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 203</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.3.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 3, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.2.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 2, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 2, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.367" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 367</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 13</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 13</bibl> Peculiar use: <cit><quote>and rather choose to hide them in a n. than amply to imbar their crooked titles,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.93" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 93</bibl></cit> (== intricacy).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>